### ===============================================
### COMPREHENSIVE DEMO TENANT SETUP
### ===============================================
### This file creates 3 fully-configured demo tenants with:
### 1. All custom field types (text, number, date, select, boolean, textarea, etc.)
### 2. Calculated fields with SpEL expressions
### 3. Business policies (DENY and WARN severity)
### 4. 15-20 sample customers, contacts, opportunities, and activities per tenant
### 5. Company branding (logo, colors, description)
### 6. Tenant settings configured

### Prerequisites:
### - Run auth.http first to get accessToken for system_admin
### - Docker Postgres must be running
### - Backend running on localhost:8080

---

### ========================================
### 1. LOGIN AS SYSTEM ADMIN
### ========================================

### Login - System Admin (demo@bocrm.com)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{demoEmail}}",
  "password": "{{demoPassword}}"
}

> {%
    client.test("Status is 200", function() {
        client.assert(response.status === 200, "Expected 200 but got " + response.status);
    });
    client.global.set("adminAccessToken", response.body.accessToken);
    client.global.set("adminTenantId", response.body.currentTenantId);
    client.log("✓ Logged in as system admin");
%}

---

### ========================================
### 2. CREATE THREE DEMO TENANTS
### ========================================

### Create Tenant 1 - Acme Tech Solutions
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/tenants
Authorization: Bearer {{adminAccessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Acme Tech Solutions"
}

> {%
    client.test("Status is 200", function() {
        client.assert(response.status === 200, "Expected 200");
    });
    client.global.set("tenant1Id", response.body.id);
    client.global.set("tenant1Name", "Acme Tech Solutions");
    client.log("✓ Created Tenant 1 (Acme Tech Solutions): ID " + response.body.id);
%}

